---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About | The Canary Institute" description="Learn about The Canary Institute's mission, team, and approach to AI safety research and policy.">
  <h1>About</h1>

  <section class="section">
    <h2>Who We Are</h2>
    <p>
      The Canary Institute is an independent, non-partisan, not-for-profit
      organization dedicated to ensuring that the development of advanced
      artificial intelligence proceeds safely and in the public interest. Our
      name reflects our purpose: like the canary in the coal mine, we aim to
      detect and communicate dangers before they become catastrophic.
    </p>
    <p>
      We were founded by researchers and policy experts who recognized that the
      rapid advancement of AI systems demanded a dedicated institution to bridge
      the gap between technical AI safety research and the public understanding
      and policy frameworks needed to act on it. The leading figures in AI
      research&mdash;including Nobel laureates, Turing Award winners, and the
      heads of major AI laboratories&mdash;have publicly stated that the
      technology they are building may pose an existential threat to humanity.
      When the architects themselves issue warnings of this gravity, civil
      society must respond with institutions equal to the challenge.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <h2>Our Approach</h2>
    <p>
      We combine rigorous technical and economic analysis with accessible public
      communication and evidence-based policy advocacy. We believe that AI
      safety is not a problem that can be solved by technologists alone&mdash;it
      requires collaboration across disciplines, sectors, and borders.
    </p>
    <p>
      We are not opposed to artificial intelligence. We are opposed to
      negligence. The potential benefits of AI are enormous, but so are the
      risks if development proceeds without adequate safeguards. Our work is
      guided by the conviction that these benefits can only be realized if the
      technology remains under meaningful human control.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <h2>Our Principles</h2>

    <div class="principles-grid">
      <div class="principle">
        <h3>Evidence Over Ideology</h3>
        <p>
          We follow the science and the data wherever they lead. We do not begin
          from a conclusion. If the evidence says the risks are lower than
          feared, we will say so. If higher, we will say that too.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="principle">
        <h3>Non-Partisan Independence</h3>
        <p>
          AI safety is not a left or right issue. It is a human issue. We accept
          no corporate funding that conditions our work, and we align with no
          political party or movement.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="principle">
        <h3>Clarity Without Distortion</h3>
        <p>
          The public deserves to understand what is happening. We translate
          technical research into accessible language without sensationalism or
          false reassurance.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="principle">
        <h3>Urgency Without Panic</h3>
        <p>
          The timelines for advanced AI capabilities are uncertain but may be
          short. This demands focused, serious action&mdash;not paralysis, not
          complacency, and not hysteria.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <h2>Team</h2>
    <p>
      Our team brings together expertise in machine learning, physics, data
      science, economics, philosophy, and public policy. Detailed team
      information is forthcoming.
    </p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .principles-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    gap: 1.5rem;
    margin-top: 1rem;
  }

  @media (min-width: 600px) {
    .principles-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    }
  }

  .principle {
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    padding: 1.5rem;
  }

  .principle h3 {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--color-dark);
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .principle p {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }
</style>
